timing_report_...lock_unrolling(25.10)  timing_report_...lock_unrolling(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_enable_clock_unrolling

Syntax
       timing_report_enable_clock_unrolling

       {true | false}

       Default : false

       Enables  the  clock unrolled reporting format that shows more intuitive
       timing reports with respect to constraints.

       When set to true, the report_timing command provides an optional format
       where the clock edge arrival times in the detailed  path  section  show
       the  worst-case  clock edge pair used for the analysis. This format can
       provide a more intuitive understanding of the clock edges used -  espe-
       cially in cases where the launch and capture clocks have different fre-
       quencies.

       When  set  to false, the detailed path section shows clock edge arrival
       times with respect to the base cycle of the clocks. Any required cycle-
       accounting adjustments are provided by the Phase Shift  and  Cycle  Ad-
       justment entries in the timing report summary section.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

